cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on modelling user voting intention in social media, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and social network analysis (SNA). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) due to the NLP aspect. The paper also involves analysis of social media data, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
